<dl id="n42020c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n42" href="#n42020c">N42 (VI.B.31)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n42all.htm#n42020c"> 20(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">D</font> mocks P.P.</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Chapter VIII. Does auricular confession bring peace to the soul?]</font> Hardly had I uttered these words, &ldquo;mocked a priest,&rdquo; when this pretended representative of the humble Jesus, turning towards me, and looking in my face, in order to know me better, asked abruptly, &ldquo;What priest did you mock, my boy?&rdquo; <small> Chiniquy, <a name="CPWC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CPWC"><cite title="source">The Priest The Woman and The Confessional</cite></a> (n.d.) 94</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
